package wamn:materializer@0.1.0;

/// The Service-first materializer (EVT-MAT, D19 v3 §5 / l5i9.17): a
/// wasi:cli/run SERVICE workload (CRD `spec.service`) — the first importer of
/// `wamn:jetstream` — that turns CDC row events into flow runs.
///
/// Per delivered event: registration match (rename-proof entity-id keying) →
/// tenant guard → causation budget (depth 16, alertable refusals) → condition
/// eval (hot-editable; filtered-out events REMAIN on the stream, so condition
/// edits replay) → deterministic `run_id = <flow>:evt:<stream_seq>` minted →
/// write-ahead run + enqueue in ONE `wamn:postgres` transaction with
/// `ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING` (the exactly-once guarantee; the JetStream dedupe
/// window is only the fast path) → post-commit doorbell ring → ack.
///
/// The decision pipeline is the PURE `wamn-materializer` crate; this component
/// is the effect shell. Identity is host-injected end-to-end: the DB tenant
/// claim and the doorbell tenant ride `wamn.tenant` workload config (never
/// guest-chosen), the schema rides `wamn.schema`, the event-plane NATS is the
/// host plugin's own connection. The guest's env (`WAMN_MAT_*`) carries only
/// what it must know to SUBSCRIBE: stream name, subject segments, its own
/// tenant label for the guard, and cadence knobs.
world materializer {
  import wamn:postgres/types@0.1.0;
  import wamn:postgres/client@0.1.0;
  import wamn:jetstream/types@0.1.0;
  import wamn:jetstream/consumer@0.1.0;
  import wamn:jetstream/doorbell@0.1.0;
}
